1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:05,005
[Jalil] <i>Jamilah… Father…</i>
<i>I already know the truth.</i>

2
00:00:05,088 --> 00:00:09,509
Doctor Teresa and Marcus…
They are my missing family.

3
00:00:09,592 --> 00:00:14,764
I am part of the syndicate formed
by Colonel Napoleon Marcelino.

4
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:17,350
[Datu Rahman] <i>The incident</i>
<i>on the M/V Doña Emilia…</i>

5
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:20,854
<i>We tried to stop the explosion,</i>
<i>but we couldn't do anything.</i>

6
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:22,063
<i>And unfortunately, that's when Victor,</i>

7
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:23,690
<i>your father, died.</i>

8
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:25,108
<i>But before he passed away,</i>

9
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:28,319
- <i>he asked me to save you and your brother.</i>
- [indistinct]

10
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:30,030
That's why I couldn't return you
to your mother,

11
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:31,614
because I didn't know where they lived.

12
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:35,243
[Datu Rahman] <i>I also had to hide</i>
<i>from the syndicate, Jalil.</i>

13
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:36,911
Change your name.

14
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:38,663
I changed it to…

15
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:40,331
- <i>Rahman Abubakar.</i>
- [inaudible]

16
00:00:40,957 --> 00:00:42,584
- [Jamilah sobs]
- [Datu Rahman] <i>Please forgive me, son.</i>

17
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:45,003
[Jalil] <i>I will punish those</i>
<i>who need to get punished.</i>

18
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:46,880
<i>So you will be set free from your past.</i>

19
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:49,048
Major Allan Espina

20
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:53,094
and Jalil Abubakar are the same person.

21
00:00:53,178 --> 00:00:54,679
[Usman] <i>You need to see this.</i>

22
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:56,181
[Nathalia] <i>I've thought about it</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

23
00:00:56,264 --> 00:00:58,349
My new Chief of Staff

24
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:01,311
<i>will be General Manuel Carillo.</i>

25
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:03,605
Now, he is more powerful.

26
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:06,316
We thought we had the upper hand,
but we didn't.

27
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:11,488
The group behind this destabilization

28
00:01:11,571 --> 00:01:13,573
is led by Hassan Wadi,

29
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:18,453
who goes by the alias
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

30
00:01:18,536 --> 00:01:20,538
He's been conspiring with
none other than his own son,

31
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:22,916
Jalil Abubakar.

32
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:24,542
You bastard!

33
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:27,879
[tense music playing]

34
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:38,014
[mysterious theme music playing]

35
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,945
[chair, computers thud]

36
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:54,197
- [Emil] Reyes!
- Bro!

37
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,365
Bro!

38
00:01:55,448 --> 00:01:58,451
- Reyes!
- Reyes, where are you going?

39
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:01,704
[Espina] Bro!

40
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:03,456
Bro!

41
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:05,458
Reyes!

42
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:13,883
[stirring music playing]

43
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:27,772
Datu Rahman, is it true?

44
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:30,275
What General Carillo said?

45
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:33,111
Datu Rahman, that's not really you, is it?

46
00:02:33,194 --> 00:02:34,404
[Norhana] Hold on.

47
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:37,866
Let's at least give him
a chance to explain.

48
00:02:37,949 --> 00:02:41,578
But how did you end up
changing your name from Hassan Wadi

49
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:44,205
if you weren't doing anything wrong?

50
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:45,748
That's ridiculous!

51
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:48,793
Sir Omar, what's the truth?

52
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:52,046
[stirring music playing]

53
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:53,798
What you heard is true.

54
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:57,844
- Hassan Wadi is Rahman's real name.
- [sighs]

55
00:02:58,636 --> 00:03:02,307
But not everything
General Carillo said is true.

56
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:05,059
What about the syndicate?

57
00:03:05,935 --> 00:03:08,021
Is it true you used to be one of them?

58
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:12,775
- [music intensifies]
- [inhales sharply]

59
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,987
Please forgive me…

60
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:20,033
for not telling you everything sooner.

61
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:21,284
[woman huffs]

62
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:26,205
I know everything
you've done for my family.

63
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,627
I just…

64
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:34,088
didn't know how to tell you.

65
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:37,508
I left that life behind a long time ago.

66
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:45,225
I changed my name to escape

67
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:51,773
and keep my former associates
from finding me.

68
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:56,694
Rahman changed a long time ago.

69
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:00,114
But after he defended the island,

70
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:02,575
the syndicate found him again.

71
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:04,118
Since then,

72
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:06,913
they've been pinning
all their crimes on him.

73
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:10,541
I hope you can forgive me.

74
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:17,799
[music becomes morose]

75
00:04:21,844 --> 00:04:24,847
[Manuel] <i>This Hassan Wadi,</i>

76
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:29,227
this criminal, this master manipulator,

77
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:33,731
<i>has been hiding in plain sight</i>

78
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:40,029
<i>under the alias Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

79
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:46,244
[breathing heavily]

80
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:51,040
Datu Rahman was the man I saw
blow up the M/V Doña Emilia.

81
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,751
[explosion]

82
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,878
But should I believe Carillo?

83
00:04:56,921 --> 00:05:00,800
What happened
to the ship wasn't an accident.

84
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:05,096
The M/V Doña Emilia was bombed.

85
00:05:05,179 --> 00:05:06,389
If Datu Rahman is guilty,

86
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:09,225
Sir Mustapha won't let him
get away with it.

87
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:14,230
[breathing heavily, grunts]

88
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:16,733
[Marcus] <i>I need to talk to Datu Rahman.</i>

89
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:18,192
<i>I need to find out the truth.</i>

90
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:21,696
[laughter]

91
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,906
- [cheering, clapping]
- General Carillo!

92
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:25,742
- [man, in English] Congratulations!
- [cheering]

93
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:28,036
- [cheering]
- [man, in English] Congrats!

94
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,829
[applause, cheering]

95
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:32,790
Now that I'm in power,

96
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:35,877
nothing can stop our plans anymore.

97
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:40,214
While everyone is consumed
with hatred for Datu Rahman,

98
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:43,051
we're building our new republic!

99
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:44,469
- [in English] Yes!
- [cheering]

100
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:46,179
[applause, cheering]

101
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:47,263
Cheers! Cheers!

102
00:05:47,346 --> 00:05:48,431
- Yes!
- Cheers!

103
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:51,350
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

104
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:54,562
- To the republic!
- To the republic!

105
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:58,691
- [dark music playing]
- [laughter, cheering]

106
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,151
‪[exhales]

107
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:03,196
‪[somber music playing]

108
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,614
- Have a drink first, Father.
- [sighs]

109
00:06:06,115 --> 00:06:07,075
[both sigh]

110
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:08,451
[knock on door]

111
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,209
- [Jamilah] Sir Marcus?
- Agent Reyes?

112
00:06:16,292 --> 00:06:19,253
[unsettling music playing]

113
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,089
Were you the one who blew up the ship?

114
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:22,381
What?

115
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:25,301
My brother died,

116
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:29,388
and my family was torn apart
because of what happened.

117
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:32,558
Tell me the truth, Datu Rahman!

118
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:33,559
Was it you?

119
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,895
Were you the reason my brother died?

120
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,939
- [Jamilah] Sir Marcus.
- Tell me!

121
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:42,276
General Carillo's accusations
against me aren't true.

122
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:47,323
I wasn't the one who blew up that ship.

123
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:51,953
I was there because I was trying
to stop the explosion.

124
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:54,247
I was with…

125
00:06:55,289 --> 00:06:57,834
my friend, Victor.

126
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,170
Victor?

127
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:02,463
Victor Reyes.

128
00:07:04,173 --> 00:07:06,843
I only found out recently
that he was your father.

129
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:13,057
[melancholic music playing]

130
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:16,769
You knew about this too?

131
00:07:17,645 --> 00:07:20,189
Doctor Teresa told me

132
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:23,693
that her long-missing husband
was also named Victor.

133
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:26,988
But this…

134
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,323
I only found out just now.

135
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,289
The syndicate deceived us.

136
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:41,752
That's why we decided to leave the group
and start a new life.

137
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:44,297
We found out they were planning
to blow up the ship

138
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:47,592
because the police had discovered
the illegal weapons

139
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:50,720
that could be used
as evidence against them.

140
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:52,221
‪[Datu Rahman inhales sharply]

141
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:56,851
We went there to stop the explosion.

142
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,186
But we were too late.

143
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:01,272
Your father died…

144
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:08,112
trying to save his wife…

145
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:10,990
and his two sons.

146
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:21,626
- [dramatic sting]
- [epic music playing]

147
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:36,015
Marcus was devastated
when he lost his brother.

148
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,935
When he lost you.

149
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:41,395
That's how much he loves you, Jalil.

150
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,773
You've been gone for 30 years.

151
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:45,483
But to this day,

152
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:48,236
he and Doctor Teresa
are still mourning you.

153
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:52,073
Do you really not want
to tell them the truth?

154
00:08:53,449 --> 00:08:54,784
[pensive music playing]

155
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,619
Jamilah, I do.

156
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:59,705
I'm tired of keeping this from them.

157
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:05,336
But General Carillo has accused me
of helping my father

158
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,838
carry out the destabilization
against the government.

159
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,967
The day after tomorrow,
they'll find out that I'm Jalil Abubakar.

160
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:13,928
Marcus will get dragged into this.

161
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:16,305
Doctor Teresa and Marcus are safer

162
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:19,183
if they know nothing
about who I really am.

163
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:22,436
They can't be connected to me.

164
00:09:23,646 --> 00:09:25,106
Please forgive me, Jalil.

165
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:27,316
[morose music playing]

166
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:31,195
So many people have suffered
because of my bad decisions.

167
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:33,281
Even your own family…

168
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:36,117
You've had to keep everything from them.

169
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,202
All because of what I've done.

170
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,455
Please forgive me.

171
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:44,292
Father.

172
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:47,086
[pensive music playing]

173
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,589
It's true that you've made mistakes.

174
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:55,386
But General Carillo
is weaponizing your mistakes

175
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:57,888
for his wicked plans.

176
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,892
So I need to stop him.

177
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:05,271
The truth will come out after all of this.

178
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:08,357
But that's not yet possible right now.

179
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:13,863
General Carillo might drag them
to his accusations against me.

180
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,782
Against us.

181
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:31,881
[sighs]

182
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:35,885
Does that mean that
your father left us because

183
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,929
he wanted to protect us
from the syndicate?

184
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:43,809
And that he died saving us?

185
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:45,019
[sighs]

186
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:47,063
[somber music playing]

187
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,689
I don't know anymore, Mom.

188
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:53,361
I don't believe General Carillo.

189
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:57,948
But my trust in Datu Rahman
is slowly wavering too.

190
00:10:58,032 --> 00:11:00,076
- Son…
- No, Mom.

191
00:11:00,951 --> 00:11:03,621
I saved Datu Rahman's life
several times already.

192
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:06,999
I also gave him a lot of chances
to tell me the truth!

193
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:10,002
But he lied to me over and over again.

194
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:11,796
He hid the truth from me.

195
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,508
[Teresa] But if…

196
00:11:15,591 --> 00:11:18,386
If Datu Rahman is telling the truth,

197
00:11:19,095 --> 00:11:22,473
then we did not only lose
your brother that night.

198
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:23,974
We lost your father as well.

199
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:27,478
We could've had a chance to be whole,

200
00:11:27,561 --> 00:11:30,606
but our family has been completely ruined

201
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:33,651
by criminals who…

202
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:34,985
[exhales deeply]

203
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:37,530
Criminals who were responsible
for what happened then.

204
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:40,741
There's only one thing
I'm sure of right now, Mom.

205
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:45,162
General Carillo is behind all of this.

206
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:47,957
[foreboding music playing]

207
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,376
That's why I have to stop him.

208
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:02,221
No matter what you do,
no matter how you interrogate me,

209
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:04,890
I'll only tell you this.

210
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:07,601
I don't know anything.

211
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:12,773
[Azuelo] We've already arrested
General Madriaga.

212
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:14,942
He already snitched on you.

213
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:16,569
So, if I were you,

214
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:19,488
I would tell the truth!

215
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,992
Your sentence might get shorter then.

216
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:27,371
Who are your co-conspirators?!

217
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:31,292
It seems like you're
in a hurry to get information.

218
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,085
- Azuelo.
- [grunts]

219
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,588
[Ocampo] Why?

220
00:12:35,671 --> 00:12:37,298
Did something happen?

221
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:40,926
Is that why you're forcing me
to give you information

222
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,887
that you need to know?

223
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,139
Why?

224
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:47,933
Are there any news?

225
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:51,896
Is there… an announcement?

226
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:53,355
How did you find out that--

227
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:56,692
I said I don't know anything!

228
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:59,153
That's why I asked you.

229
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:01,906
[stirring music playing]

230
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:06,452
Don't threaten me.

231
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:09,288
I pity you.

232
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:13,667
Because in just a few more days,

233
00:13:13,751 --> 00:13:16,086
I'll get out of here.

234
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,506
- Why are you so sure of that?
- [Ocampo scoffs]

235
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:22,885
We don't know.

236
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:26,847
I might replace you
and take your position soon.

237
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:33,187
[chair scraping]

238
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:34,688
You bastard!

239
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:37,358
What are you up to, huh?!

240
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:39,777
How can you be so sure

241
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:42,071
that you'll ever get out of here?!

242
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:43,322
[grunts]

243
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:50,412
Because I don't know nothing
about what you're saying.

244
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:53,874
But you…

245
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:58,879
You arrested me
without any case against me.

246
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:02,591
Let's see what will happen to you.

247
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:05,594
[Azuelo grunting]

248
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:07,304
[objects clattering]

249
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:12,643
[music intensifies]

250
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:20,317
Was General Carillo the leader
of your syndicate back then, Father?

251
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:23,487
I don't know him.

252
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:26,824
The person I know is Colonel Marcelino.

253
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:30,911
If that's the case,
then why is he blaming you?

254
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:34,999
If he'll make up a story
to get you in jail…

255
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:36,375
Why would he do that, Father?

256
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:39,962
The only reason I can think of

257
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:42,506
is that he's now the one
running the syndicate.

258
00:14:43,173 --> 00:14:46,760
He's continuing the organization
and the advocacy

259
00:14:46,844 --> 00:14:48,804
that Colonel Marcelino started.

260
00:14:49,847 --> 00:14:51,390
[knocking on door]

261
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:53,767
It's Jalil.

262
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,019
[man] Jamilah?

263
00:14:55,102 --> 00:15:00,065
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [Jamilah gasps]

264
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:03,569
Father!

265
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:06,906
Who are you? What are you doing here?

266
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:14,580
Do you know who I am, Hassan Wadi?

267
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:17,791
- Major Dante?
- [Dante] General.

268
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:20,669
General Dante Guerzon.

269
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:24,465
I'm a close friend of Marcelo Napoleon…

270
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:29,094
who was the brother
of General Manuel Carillo.

271
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:34,391
[dramatic stinging]

272
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:37,436
‪[dramatic sting]

273
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:45,945
Manuel was the one
who planned all of this.

274
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:50,115
Manuel is Napoleon's
illegitimate half-brother.

275
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:53,994
They built the syndicate together.

276
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,287
[suspenseful music continues]

277
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:58,415
Manuel got too aggressive.

278
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:01,377
And that was what they often argued about.

279
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:04,505
I'm also convinced that

280
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:06,924
Manuel was the one who killed the doctors

281
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,135
on a medical mission in Mindanao…

282
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:12,221
to spill blood.

283
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:15,766
[suspenseful music continues]

284
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:22,439
[Dante] It was also his idea
to blow up the ship.

285
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:28,988
But he used Napoleon's name
while giving out orders.

286
00:16:29,071 --> 00:16:32,616
The police got tipped that
there's a weapons shipment here.

287
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:35,369
They're already waiting
for the ship to dock at the pier.

288
00:16:35,452 --> 00:16:36,954
The reason why Major planted a bomb here

289
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:39,498
was to erase all the evidence
that pointed to him.

290
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:43,377
[grunting] A lot
of innocent people will die!

291
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:44,461
That includes my family!

292
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,171
- [breathing heavily]
- So we have to find the bomb,

293
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,258
to defuse it and save everyone here!

294
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:52,511
[explosions]

295
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:55,472
[panting]

296
00:16:55,556 --> 00:16:56,932
Victor!

297
00:16:57,683 --> 00:16:58,726
Victor, let's go!

298
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:00,811
[suspenseful music continues]

299
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:04,690
When Napoleon found out what Manuel did,

300
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:06,984
they had a huge fight.

301
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:10,738
Eventually, Napoleon died.

302
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:15,617
No one else could do that
aside from Manuel.

303
00:17:16,118 --> 00:17:19,163
He killed his own brother.

304
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:23,709
I also suspect that

305
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:27,629
it was also Manuel who killed
his foster child, Lara.

306
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:39,266
Why are you telling me this now?

307
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:43,228
Because I know about everything
you're going through right now.

308
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,649
They want you to take all the blame

309
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,359
for everything they have done.

310
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,862
They're using you as their fall guy.

311
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:56,450
I also know that you want
to expose the whole truth.

312
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:01,330
How can I make sure

313
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:04,166
that I can trust you?

314
00:18:05,459 --> 00:18:08,045
How would I know if this
isn't part of your plan?

315
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,381
I already parted ways with Manuel.

316
00:18:12,883 --> 00:18:15,094
I'm now one of his targets.

317
00:18:21,016 --> 00:18:23,894
I'm sorry for holding you
hostage back then.

318
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:27,606
[Axl] Whether or not you believe me,

319
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:29,858
I've changed already.

320
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:33,278
I only want one thing now.

321
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:37,658
To take revenge on the animals
who killed my brothers.

322
00:18:37,741 --> 00:18:39,076
Wait a second.

323
00:18:40,869 --> 00:18:42,329
Shouldn't you be dead already?

324
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:46,542
Everyone saw you get shot in the head.

325
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,168
What happened? How are you still alive?

326
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:49,753
I don't know either.

327
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:51,922
When I woke up,

328
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,216
I was in a safe house.

329
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:57,052
The bullet grazed me here.

330
00:18:57,886 --> 00:18:59,346
I wasn't fatally shot.

331
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:02,266
But I almost died.

332
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:06,520
Thankfully, General Guerzon
looked after me.

333
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:09,857
[stirring music playing]

334
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,484
[doctor] General Guerzon.

335
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:14,153
Axl Rosales is still alive.

336
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:17,948
[groans]

337
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:19,783
I'm glad you're awake.

338
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:24,913
We have a lot to talk about, Axl Rosales.

339
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:26,623
Who are you?

340
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:28,917
Where am I?

341
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:32,754
General Guerzon just told me

342
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:34,965
that my siblings were dead.

343
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:38,051
[sobs] Jovi…

344
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:41,555
and Tommy.

345
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:44,933
Where are your parents?

346
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,937
Do they know you're still alive?

347
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:50,606
[sniffles] No.

348
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:52,482
[sniffles]

349
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:53,901
No.

350
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:54,943
[sniffles]

351
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:57,821
I can't visit my mother because
she might get caught up in this.

352
00:19:58,989 --> 00:20:00,157
[Axl sniffles]

353
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:03,952
I know what I'm doing will get me killed,

354
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:07,414
but I'll make sure

355
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:12,211
I take as many of them
to hell with me as I can.

356
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:17,758
I know you're doing this
to get justice for your siblings.

357
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,511
I hope you succeed.

358
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:28,227
You work with Marcus Reyes' mother?

359
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:32,272
Yes. Why?

360
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:34,274
Tell them

361
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:39,404
the traitor in their ranks

362
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:44,201
is SPO4 Felix Domingo.

363
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:46,954
[tense music swells]

364
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:48,705
[playful sounds]

365
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:51,166
Cuchy…

366
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:54,378
General Carillo is planning something.

367
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:57,589
So just a little more…

368
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:03,845
I can finally get my revenge
on Jalil Abubakar.

369
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:10,477
You saw how badly
he wounded me, didn't you?

370
00:21:12,562 --> 00:21:13,563
[snickers]

371
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:15,649
[in English] Good luck.

372
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:20,362
[morose music playing]

373
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:21,738
[music becomes unsettling]

374
00:21:21,822 --> 00:21:23,156
[Felix] Cuchy!

375
00:21:23,907 --> 00:21:25,158
Cuchy!

376
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:27,286
Cuchy!

377
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:28,370
[in English] Baby girl!

378
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:33,041
Cuchy!

379
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:35,877
[in English] Cuchy, baby girl!

380
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:38,338
Have you seen a dog?

381
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:40,632
No, sorry.

382
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:42,384
My Cuchy!

383
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:44,845
Cuchy!

384
00:21:46,930 --> 00:21:51,310
[unsettling music playing]

385
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:54,021
[exhales]

386
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:56,440
Cuchy, are you okay?

387
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,984
[sighs]

388
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:01,028
Cuchy, I missed you so much.

389
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:03,697
Cuchy.

390
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:05,073
[sighs]

391
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:12,706
In the next few days, they might
issue an arrest warrant for me.

392
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:15,417
They could easily have me killed.

393
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:19,129
I won't be able to defend myself.

394
00:22:20,797 --> 00:22:23,258
We won't let them take you, Rahman.

395
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:24,509
‪[tense music playing]

396
00:22:25,469 --> 00:22:26,678
Omar…

397
00:22:27,888 --> 00:22:28,972
Don't.

398
00:22:29,556 --> 00:22:31,767
The government is backing them.

399
00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:34,936
The only thing I can do now

400
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,355
is reveal everything I know
and tell the whole truth.

401
00:22:37,439 --> 00:22:39,274
[sighs]

402
00:22:39,357 --> 00:22:41,735
I know someone who can help you.

403
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:46,156
Whatever happens to me, Omar,

404
00:22:46,907 --> 00:22:49,701
I'm entrusting my children
to you and Norhana.

405
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:50,869
[breathes deeply]

406
00:22:50,952 --> 00:22:54,331
Come on, Rahman.
Don't say things like that.

407
00:22:54,414 --> 00:22:56,124
We'll get through this.

408
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:57,209
[in Arabic] God willing.

409
00:22:58,126 --> 00:22:59,669
[in Arabic] God willing.

410
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:03,215
Thank you for everything.

411
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:07,844
[tense music playing]

412
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:15,143
[pensive music playing]

413
00:23:26,404 --> 00:23:27,239
[sighs]

414
00:23:27,322 --> 00:23:33,912
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

415
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:38,250
♪ <i>The throne a tyrant playing king</i> ♪

416
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:48,176
♪ <i>Has its limits</i> ♪

417
00:23:50,387 --> 00:23:52,722
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio ends]

418
00:23:52,806 --> 00:23:53,682
How are you?

419
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:57,060
[glum music playing]

420
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,814
Carillo covers his tracks too well.

421
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:04,860
No matter how hard I look,
I can't find a single trace of him.

422
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:07,988
[breathes deeply]

423
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:10,824
But I also know this
isn't the time to lose hope.

424
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:17,873
I still believe Carillo is the mastermind
behind all of this.

425
00:24:18,456 --> 00:24:19,291
I do too.

426
00:24:19,374 --> 00:24:22,252
That's why we have to stop him.

427
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:26,756
But how?

428
00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:32,220
[phone buzzing]

429
00:24:35,473 --> 00:24:38,560
[reporter] <i>Datu Rahman Abubakar</i>
<i>is about to speak!</i>

430
00:24:38,643 --> 00:24:41,188
<i>He'll answer every allegation against him</i>

431
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:46,735
<i>in an exclusive tell-all interview</i>
<i>on</i> Inside the Truth with Maya Mae Kalaw.

432
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:52,115
[tense music playing]

433
00:24:55,076 --> 00:24:56,286
[door clicks shut]

434
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,496
[Felix inhales deeply]

435
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:01,249
Cuchy… My Cuchy.

436
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:03,919
Where are you?

437
00:25:04,002 --> 00:25:05,629
[sighs deeply]

438
00:25:05,712 --> 00:25:08,882
[phone vibrating]

439
00:25:12,302 --> 00:25:13,762
[in English] Hello, General.

440
00:25:13,845 --> 00:25:18,850
[stirring music playing]

441
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:21,686
[in English] Yes, sir.

442
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:34,199
[tense music playing]

443
00:25:35,575 --> 00:25:38,245
[Jalil] <i>Father… What are you planning?</i>

444
00:25:44,793 --> 00:25:46,503
[line ringing]

445
00:25:46,586 --> 00:25:48,255
- [in English] Sir, excuse me.
- [sighs]

446
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:49,589
I'm just going to attach your lapel mic.

447
00:25:51,549 --> 00:25:53,510
[phone ringing]

448
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:00,976
Jalil.

449
00:26:01,643 --> 00:26:03,436
I was just about to call you.

450
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:06,314
Jamilah, is Father with you?

451
00:26:07,023 --> 00:26:07,983
[Jamilah] <i>Yes, Jalil.</i>

452
00:26:08,066 --> 00:26:12,696
Uh, we're here
at Miss Maya Mae Kalaw's studio.

453
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:14,948
What are you doing there?

454
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:21,496
Father wants to reveal
everything he knows.

455
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:23,248
What?!

456
00:26:24,124 --> 00:26:27,585
Jamilah, our father's life is in danger.

457
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:28,920
Why would he do that?!

458
00:26:29,004 --> 00:26:30,755
[breathes deeply] Jalil…

459
00:26:31,965 --> 00:26:35,176
General Guerzon came
to our house last night.

460
00:26:36,678 --> 00:26:38,054
General Guerzon?

461
00:26:38,138 --> 00:26:39,848
[Jamilah] Yes, Jalil.

462
00:26:39,931 --> 00:26:42,976
And after they talked last night,

463
00:26:43,059 --> 00:26:45,103
that's what Father decided to do.

464
00:26:46,021 --> 00:26:47,522
Jalil, one more thing.

465
00:26:48,523 --> 00:26:52,152
General Guerzon
was with Axl Rosales last night.

466
00:26:52,235 --> 00:26:53,486
What?!

467
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:55,113
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil, he's alive.</i>

468
00:26:55,697 --> 00:27:00,452
And he wants me to tell you and Sir Marcus
that there's a traitor in your ranks.

469
00:27:00,535 --> 00:27:01,369
‪[heavy breathing]

470
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:07,083
It's SPO4 Felix Domingo.

471
00:27:07,751 --> 00:27:10,837
[tense music playing]

472
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,047
[slams]

473
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:17,135
[man, in English] Okay,
stand by, everyone.

474
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:19,429
[in English] We are about to air.

475
00:27:19,512 --> 00:27:21,097
[in English] Overhead clapping.

476
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:22,932
[in English] Okay!

477
00:27:24,851 --> 00:27:30,023
[tense music continues]

478
00:27:45,038 --> 00:27:50,251
[tense music continues]

479
00:28:12,565 --> 00:28:15,485
[in English] Please welcome
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

480
00:28:15,568 --> 00:28:17,529
[shouts] Dang it!

481
00:28:17,612 --> 00:28:19,406
[Datu Rahman]
<i>I was involved with a syndicate.</i>

482
00:28:19,906 --> 00:28:23,284
But what General Carillo
is saying about the bombing…

483
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:25,203
I had nothing to do with those.

484
00:28:25,286 --> 00:28:29,082
He was the mastermind behind
everything that's happening now.

485
00:28:29,165 --> 00:28:30,583
The former head

486
00:28:30,667 --> 00:28:32,168
- [gunshot]
- of the syndicate--

487
00:28:32,961 --> 00:28:35,130
[wailing] Father!

488
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:36,297
Father!

489
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:37,424
[Jalil] <i>Help!</i>

490
00:28:37,507 --> 00:28:40,719
[crying, bawling]

491
00:28:41,344 --> 00:28:43,012
[Espina] <i>I'd understand</i>
<i>if you're mad with me.</i>

492
00:28:43,096 --> 00:28:46,891
But everything I showed you,
all of it was real.

493
00:28:47,642 --> 00:28:49,561
I didn't just see you as a friend.

494
00:28:50,645 --> 00:28:51,980
I came to see you as my brother.
